{{Infobox language |name=Araweté |nativename= |region=[[Brazil]] |speakers=280 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Tupian languages|Tupian]] |fam2=[[Tupi–Guarani languages|Tupi–Guarani]] |fam3=Xingu |iso3=awt |glotto=araw1273 |glottorefname=Araweté }}
'''Araweté''' is a [[Tupi–Guaraní languages|Tupi–Guaraní language]] of the state of [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], in the Amazon region of [[Brazil]]. Nearly all speakers were monolingual in 1986.
