The '''Bulaka River''' languages are a pair of closely related [[Papuan languages]], [[Yelmek language|Yelmek]] and [[Maklew language|Maklew]], on the [[Bulaka River]] in Indonesian [[West Papua (region)|West Papua]]. They are ethnically Yab (Jab); their speech is ''Yabga (Jabga)''.  Ross (2005) tentatively includes them in the proposed [[Trans-Fly – Bulaka River languages|Trans-Fly – Bulaka River]] family, but Usher, who reconstructs the family, retains Bulaka River as a primary language family.<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/newguineaworld/families/bulaka-river]</ref>

