{{Orphan|date=November 2012}}

'''Heni Te Kiri Karamu''' (1840&ndash;1933), known sometimes as ''Heni Pore'' was a notable New Zealand tribal leader, teacher, warrior and interpreter. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, she identified with the [[Ngati Uenukukopako]] and [[Te Arawa]] [[iwi]]. She was born in [[Kaitaia]], [[Northland Region|Northland]], [[New Zealand]] in 1840.<ref name="DNZB Te Kiri Karamu">{{DNZB|title=Heni Te Kiri Karamu|first= Steven|last= Oliver|id=1t43|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

