{{unreferenced|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox language family |name=Macro-Warpean |acceptance=controversial |region=South America |familycolor=American |family = Proposed language family |child1=[[Muran languages|Mura]]–[[Matanawi language|Matanawi]] |child2=''[[Huarpe language|Huarpe]]'' |glotto=none }}
'''Macro-Warpean''' is a provisional proposal by Kaufman (1994) that connected the extinct Huarpe language with the previously connected [[Muran languages|Muran]] and [[Matanawi language|Matanawí]] ''(Mura–Matanawí)''. [[Morris Swadesh]] had included Huarpe in his [[Macro-Jibaro]] proposal.
